WEBVTT

00:00:00.962 --> 00:00:04.125
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:00:04.686 --> 00:00:18.380
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization, using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:00:19.121 --> 00:00:26.649
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:00:26.709 --> 00:00:27.890
Today,

00:00:27.970 --> 00:00:35.998
We invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:00:40.902 --> 00:00:41.543
Peace be with you.

00:00:41.883 --> 00:00:46.608
Friends, we've come today to one of my favorite feasts, this feast of the epiphany.

00:00:47.328 --> 00:00:53.154
What is it about this story of the kings, the magi, the wise men that has so captivated us?

00:00:53.334 --> 00:00:57.298
I mean, for the past 20 centuries, poets and painters and

00:00:57.602 --> 00:01:01.488
Sculptors and mystics have been fascinated by this story.

00:01:02.189 --> 00:01:06.836
The whole Cologne Cathedral in Germany, you know, it's sort of predicated upon the three wise men.

00:01:06.856 --> 00:01:08.578
They claim the relics of them are there.

00:01:09.379 --> 00:01:09.860
What is it?

00:01:09.940 --> 00:01:10.501
What is it?

00:01:10.601 --> 00:01:13.225
Why is a story so entrancing?

00:01:13.986 --> 00:01:21.737
Well, I think it's some ways it's telling the whole spiritual life that you could read the dynamics of the spiritual life off of the story very well.

00:01:22.278 --> 00:01:24.882
I want to just hit a couple of highlights.

00:01:25.442 --> 00:01:31.070
First, I think this story of the Magi is all about what I'll call the longing.

00:01:32.212 --> 00:01:35.416
You know, we desire all kinds of things in life and we seek them and we find them.

00:01:36.037 --> 00:01:53.362
But underneath all of our particular desires and particular longings, there's this great longing, this ache of the heart, this desire for, call what you want, fulfillment for peace,

00:01:54.786 --> 00:01:54.986
C.S.

00:01:55.147 --> 00:01:59.714
Lewis called it joy, and he named it every particular way.

00:02:01.036 --> 00:02:15.399
This longing that's awakened in us at certain points in life, when we're aware in a kind of oblique way of what we want, but we also know we'll never be able to attain it completely.

00:02:16.421 --> 00:02:22.290
That unfulfillable longing, at least in this life,

00:02:22.722 --> 00:02:23.703
He called joy.

00:02:24.063 --> 00:02:28.087
So it doesn't mean that superficial, you know, I'm happy clappy because something nice happened to me.

00:02:28.668 --> 00:02:31.511
It's something weirder and deeper and stranger.

00:02:31.551 --> 00:02:39.879
It's what Augustine talked about when he said, Lord, you made us for yourself and therefore our heart is restless till it rests in thee.

00:02:40.920 --> 00:02:42.942
See, it's permanently restless in this life.

00:02:43.643 --> 00:02:50.610
So even as we glimpse what we want, we have a sense of what the fulfillment is, we also know we're never going to get there.

00:02:51.298 --> 00:03:02.290
So think of the Mage I know, astrologers, astronomers surveying the night sky, and they're looking with a scientific spirit that's true.

00:03:02.810 --> 00:03:07.836
But in the deeper way, they're looking for God's sign, for meaning.

00:03:08.636 --> 00:03:10.799
What is God trying to communicate?

00:03:11.960 --> 00:03:16.064
Well, I just love this part of the story, and we should never let go of that.

00:03:16.825 --> 00:03:17.746
It's one of the most

00:03:17.954 --> 00:03:21.338
kind of precious and beautiful and rare things in life.

00:03:22.319 --> 00:03:33.513
One of the many reasons I hate secularism is secularism as an ideology is trying to stamp this out, trying to convince us that there's nothing to it.

00:03:34.074 --> 00:03:40.822
It's a holdover from the primitive side of the primitive time in the human development or something.

00:03:41.563 --> 00:03:43.025
Resist that, everybody.

00:03:43.065 --> 00:03:47.090
Resist that with all your heart because it's what makes us

00:03:47.586 --> 00:03:57.277
Really human is this infinite longing, this deep ache of the heart, this quest for God.

00:03:57.437 --> 00:04:04.425
Don't listen to the avatars of secularism that want to suppress that.

00:04:06.227 --> 00:04:15.858
You know, so the magi look and they long and they seek and they find this enigmatic sign, you know, so the star

00:04:16.546 --> 00:04:18.850
Well, it's the star of the newborn king.

00:04:19.070 --> 00:04:21.073
Well, yeah, I guess.

00:04:22.315 --> 00:04:25.500
I mean, it's not God in his fullness.

00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:27.343
It's an indication.

00:04:27.403 --> 00:04:32.591
It's a beautiful but same-time ambiguous indication.

00:04:32.611 --> 00:04:38.981
That's what it's like, isn't it, in our quest for God as we get signs and hints.

00:04:40.664 --> 00:04:43.508
But they follow it, and that's beautiful about them.

00:04:43.689 --> 00:04:44.530
That's beautiful.

00:04:45.122 --> 00:04:46.544
They don't suppress or deny it.

00:04:47.084 --> 00:04:50.688
They follow this indication from God.

00:04:51.949 --> 00:04:58.697
And it takes them over desert land, and as I said, all travel in the ancient world was dangerous.

00:04:59.738 --> 00:05:01.140
A hard coming we had of it.

00:05:01.160 --> 00:05:02.561
That's T.S.

00:05:03.162 --> 00:05:06.866
Eliot's great poem begins, you know, the difficulty of the journey.

00:05:07.567 --> 00:05:11.431
And think if someone asks them, well, what are you guys looking for?

00:05:11.511 --> 00:05:12.172
Where are you going?

00:05:12.352 --> 00:05:14.354
Well, we're following a star.

00:05:14.466 --> 00:05:15.968
to find a newborn king.

00:05:15.988 --> 00:05:19.914
A bit like Noah building the ark.

00:05:19.994 --> 00:05:21.396
